<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Banesto Chairman on Pending Sale of Media Assets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Banesto Chairman on Pending Sale of Media Assets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505211294 Madrid Teletexto TVE in Spanish 1817 GMT 25 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid Teletexto TVE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Alfredo Saenz [chairman of Banesto] 
speaking today in the Congress of Deputies, the sale of 
Banesto's stake in media companies will "generate losses." 
  Banesto's chairman confirmed that negotiations for selling 
Banesto's stake in Antena 3, Grupo Zeta, and Tele 5 are under 
way with Bankers Trust. The American bank will not be 
responsible for the sale of EL MUNDO and EPOCA. 
  According to Saenz, the Banesto corporation "does not 
correspond to what an industrial group should be" and until 
definitive data is available, its 1993 loses may amount to 
120,000 million pesetas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

