<H3> <TI>   Russian Officials Reject Return of Karelia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Officials Reject Return of Karelia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505174194 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1300 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian parliamentarians reject the idea of 
returning Karelia to Finland. The Diet Foreign Affairs 
Committee has had talks in Moscow with representatives of the 
Russian Duma on this issue. Diet Speaker Pertti Paasio says 
that discussions on changing the borders are perceived as 
negative and there is no willingness to hold such talks. 
According to the Duma representatives, however, there can be 
discussions on cooperation in developing Karelia. Foreign 
Ministry official Joern Donner discussed the Karelia question in 
Moscow. 

</TEXT>

