<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Comments on UN Cyprus Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Comments on UN Cyprus Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2605074894 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1930 GMT 25 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2605074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkish Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has said that 
it will not be beneficial for the UN secretary general to 
present a report to the UN Security Council while talks on 
confidence-building measures are continuing. Cetin departed for 
Paris to attend the opening conference of the European Stability 
Pact. 
  In a predeparture news conference at Ankara's Esenboga 
Airport, Cetin answered a question on the report by UN Secretary 
General Butrus-Ghali. He said: The report has not yet been 
published. Actually, publishing a report when talks are 
continuing may harm the negotiations. For this reason, the 
report should be published after the talks end. 
  In answer to another question, Cetin reiterated that 
President Rauf Denktas will go to Turkey over the weekend and 
meet with President Suleyman Demirel. 

</TEXT>

