  [Text] The peace negotiations involving the legal 
representatives of Bosnia-Herzegovina, the Serbian aggressor, 
and the contact group are continuing in the French town of 
Talloires. According to sources close to the negotiators, the 
talks so far have mainly focused on the contentious territorial 
division and the future political setup of Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The Croatian and Bosniak delegation, for the sake of peace, 
expressed readiness to compromise regarding the territorial 
division, and have moved slightly closer to the 51-49 percent 
division, in accordance with the ministerial agreement in Geneva. 

