<H3> <TI>   Government Welcomes UN Package on Straits Traffic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Welcomes UN Package on Straits Traffic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2505184794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2505184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Turkey has welcomed the fact that the UN 
International Maritime Organization accepted the package of 
rules and proposals to enhance the safety of passages through 
the Istanbul and Canakkale Straits. 
  A Foreign Ministry statement noted that regulating the 
traffic in the straits will benefit all interested parties. The 
statement remarked that the new statute pertaining to the 
passage through the straits was prepared in line with basic 
international rules of law, which stipulate that every country 
can determine the procedures in the waters under its own 
sovereignty in order to ensure maritime safety and environmental 
protection. This statute will go into effect on 1 July 1994, 
the statement noted, adding that the new statute will continue 
to adhere meticulously to the Montreux Convention, as was the 
case in the past. 

</TEXT>

