<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   European Stability Conference Opens in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    European Stability Conference Opens in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Turkey Pledges Cooperation </H4>

<F P=102> TA2605153294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1440 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2605153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, May 26 (AA) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin 
said on Thursday [26 May] that the initiatives taken toward 
Europe's security and stability were very appropriate. 
  Speaking during European Stability Conference, Cetin 
revealed 
Turkey's views. 
  Cetin said the violence and ethnic cleaning in Bosnia has 
not 
been responded to adding that the bloodshed in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina has not ended yet. 
  Cetin said Europe is passing through a hard transition 
period. 
  `The problems created after the collapse of iron curtain 
need 
attention,' Cetin said. 
  He said the incidents happening in Bosnia today create 
dangerous examples for future `extreme nationalism, religious 
and cultural intolerance and racism which could arise again in 
various places in Europe.' 
  During his speech Cetin stressed good-neighborly relations 
and the importance of regional cooperation. 
  He said Turkey is ready to contribute to regional 
cooperation 
programs within the framework of European Stability Agreement. 
  Turkey is an associate member of European Union and aims at 
full membership. 

</TEXT>

