  [Text] Cyprus wants to contribute as much as possible to 
improving security and stability in Europe and looks forward to 
a further strengthening of its relations with Europe, and 
particularly with the European Union. 
  This was stressed today by Foreign Minister Alekos 
Mikhailidhis during his speech at a conference on stability in 
Europe that is being held in Paris. 
  Referring to the Cyprus issue, the foreign minister stressed 
that for 20 years Cyprus has lived the tragic results of the 
lack of strong mechanisms to prevent expansionism and punish 
violations of international law. He also said that Cyprus is an 
example of a violation of borders and incitement of minority 
problems to facilitate expansionist designs. 

