  [Excerpt] Portuguese Foreign Minister Durao Barroso says 
there is no peace in Angola for the present, because the 
Angolans themselves are blocking the process. The foreign 
minister also says that he is pessimistic about the future of 
negotiations between UNITA [National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola] and the Luanda government: 
  [Begin Barroso recording] There was an extraordinary 
international investment in Angola; however, if the Angolans 
themselves or part of them want to continue the war, we cannot 
avoid it. We continue searching for a solution and continue 
encouraging both sides to make an effort and be more flexible. 
While there was somewhat more optimistic news in the past few 
days, we continue to be rather pessimistic about a global, 
definite solution being found for the Angolan problem. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

