<H3> <TI>   Suspected Bosnian Serb War Criminal Arrested </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Suspected Bosnian Serb War Criminal Arrested </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505104394 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 25 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU2505104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["wor." report: "War Atrocities: Serb Arrested"] </F>
  [Text] Salzburg -- A Bosnian Serb for whom an international 
arrest warrant had been issued and who is accused of serious war 
crimes was arrested in Salzburg last Friday [21 May] and taken 
into custody the following day pending trial. Dusko Cvjetkovic, 
26, is said to have directed a "paramilitary operation" as the 
leader of a unit of Bosnian Serbs in the Bosnian village of 
Kucice on 14 July 1992, a spokesman for the Salzburg Provincial 
Court stated on Tuesday. Preliminary investigations for 
genocide, murder, and arson are being made against Cvjetkovic. 
If these accusations are confirmed in the further 
investigations, charges within the framework of substitute 
jurisdiction may be brought against the Serb in Austria. 

</TEXT>

