<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-103 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  26 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Returns From NATO Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Returns From NATO Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2605185194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2605185194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] National Defense Minister Mehmet Golhan has 
declared that in addition to the civilian sectors, the National 
Defense Ministry and the Chief of the General Staff's Office are 
seriously applying measures to curb expenditures. Golhan 
returned to Turkey after attending the NATO Defense Planning 
Committee and the Nuclear Planning Group spring meetings held in 
Brussels. 
  In a statement at Ankara's Esenboga Airport, Golhan reported 
that, just like Turkey, almost all countries in the world are 
experiencing economic difficulties this year and consequently 
defense budgets are being cut. Golhan remarked that after 
improving its economy, Turkey can easily purchase the weapons 
and equipment it needs without grants or military aid. 
  Commenting on the Defense Planning Committee meetings, 
Golhan 
explained that the agreements reached regarding the 
implementation of the decisions adopted during the NATO summit 
last January as well as the situation in the former Yugoslavia 
were reviewed and the NATO force goals for 1994 were approved. 
The work to be done to prevent the proliferation of mass 
destruction weapons was also assessed, Golhan reported. 
  [Begin Golhan recording] The subject was extremely important 
for Turkey, because there are countries in our geographic region 
that want to buy these mass destruction weapons and even wish to 
possess the means to launch them. Therefore, this matter is 
being pursued with sensitivity. 
  In my speech, I mentioned these issues and declared that we 
will always make constructive contributions to the work on the 
subject. [end recording] 
  The defense minister remarked that the Nuclear Planning 
Group 
meeting focused on controlling the nuclear weapons in the world 
and removing their warheads. 

</TEXT>

