<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mentese: Emigration to Iraq `Another PKK Tactic' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mentese: Emigration to Iraq `Another PKK Tactic' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2605163394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1550 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2605163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 26 (AA) -- Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese said on Thursday [26 May] that the emigration of 
civilians from eastern and southeastern Anatolia to northern 
Iraq is another tactic of the separatist terrorist organization 
PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan]. 
  Speaking at parliament's general council Mentese refused the 
claims that the government was pursuing those emigrating to 
northern Iraq. 
  `The PKK called these people there to provide international 
support and to make propaganda but still Turkey calls these 
people back,' Mentese said. 
  He said the PKK initiated all the incidents in eastern and 
southeastern Anatolia and massacred children, women and old 
people there. 

</TEXT>

