<F P=106> [By Parliamentary Staff, PRESS ASSOCIATION News] </F>
  [Text] The Government tonight announced a fresh order for 
RAF [Royal Air Force] missiles awarded to British Aerospace. 
  Defence Procurement Minister of State Jonathan Aitken said 
in 
a Commons written reply: "The contract for development and 
production of an initial batch of Advanced Short-Range 
Air-to-Air Missiles awarded to British Aerospace in March 1992 
is proceeding well." 
  He added: "Following a recent review of the operational 
requirements of the RAF's Harrier and new European Fighter 
aircraft, the contract for the follow-on order of a further 
quantity of missiles has been awarded to British Aerospace." 
  Mr Aitken said the 66 million pound order was "excellent 
news" for British industry. 

