<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suessmuth Meets With Latvian Parliament Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Suessmuth Meets With Latvian Parliament Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505165094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1204 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Bundestag President Rita Suessmuth 
met the Latvian Saeima Chairman Anatolijs Gorbunovs in Bonn 
today. Gorbunovs briefed Suessmuth on the most recent political 
and economic developments in his country. He also spoke of the 
problems regarding the return of Russian troops still in Latvia, 
the Bundestag press office announced. 
  Frau Suessmuth stressed during the talks that Latvia's 
regained independence could not be endangered by controversial 
questions which remain between Russia and the Baltic states. 
The two politicians also discussed the possibility of 
integrating Latvia into Europe and the development of political 
and parliamentary relations between the two states. 
  Gorbunovs is in Germany for a four-day visit at the 
invitation of the Bundestag president. 

</TEXT>

