GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Italian Foreign Minister Antonio Martino who is 
currently in Paris attending the Conference on European 
Stability, has called the remarks of French President Francois 
Mitterrand unacceptable. Mitterrand, referring to the new 
Italian Government and the figure of Silvio Berlusconi, spoke of 
a fearful inroad on democracy. Martino said that these remarks 
were isolated and were the only ones uttered by a head of state. 
[passage omitted] 

