<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Receives FYROM's PM Crvenkovski </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Receives FYROM's PM Crvenkovski </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605145194 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2605145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Crvenkovski Received by Berlusconi"] </F>
  [Excerpt] The newly appointed Italian Prime Minister 
Silvio Berlusconi received his Macedonian [[The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] counterpart, Branko Crvenkovski, 
yesterday. This is Berlusconi's first meeting with a foreign 
prime minister visiting Italy. He was informed on the situation 
in Macedonia and previous bilateral relations between the two 
countries. They also talked about the realization of the 
promised aid by the EU [European Union] and Berlusconi assured 
his country will do everything in its powers to accelerate it. 
Mr. Berlusconi greeted the idea of an East-West corridor, 
supposed to establish traffic and telecommunication links 
between Italy, Albania, Macedonia, Bulgaria, and Turkey. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

