<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demirel Reacts to U.S. Aid Cut, Cyprus Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2605123794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2605123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpts] President Suleyman Demirel has stated that he 
referred back to the Assembly the bill on housing for civil 
servants because it would exacerbate already difficult 
conditions in Turkey. Demirel held a breakfast meeting with 
reporters in Isparta. [passage omitted] 
  Reacting to a 25 percent cutback of U.S. aid to Turkey, 
Demirel said claims of human rights violations and the Cyprus 
issue were given as the reasons for the aid cut. Stressing that 
there is no question of Turkey violating human rights, Demirel 
said that the same measures used against human rights violations 
in the United States are being implemented in Turkey. 
  On the Cyprus impasse, Demirel said that Turkey is not 
responsible for the stalemate. 

</TEXT>

