<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO To Control Troops in East in 1995 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO To Control Troops in East in 1995 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505122194 Hamburg DPA in German 1053 GMT 25 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2505122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels -- Germany has informed NATO that the 
operational part of the German Army in the new laender is to be 
put under the control of the Western alliance as of the 
beginning of 1995. This has emerged from alliance circles after 
the meeting of the NATO Cooperation Council in Brussels on 
Wednesday [25 May]. 
  Germany had agreed with the former victorious nations that 
its troops in the former GDR should remain outside the 
integrated NATO military structure at first. After the 
withdrawal of the Russian troops from eastern Germany, Germany 
will be free to decide. 
  The details still need to be agreed upon with NATO. Another 
open question is which locations will be available to the 
Western alliance. The number of joint maneuvers will also have 
to be decided. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

