<H3> <TI>   Trade Unions Nominate Schulte for DGB Chairmanship </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Unions Nominate Schulte for DGB Chairmanship </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2205140694 Hamburg DPA in German 1221 GMT 22 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2205140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Berlin -- Dieter Schulze, 54, has been nominated as 
the official candidate to succeed Heinz-Werner Meyer, the leader 
of the German Trade Union Federation [DGB] who died two weeks 
ago. The chairmen of the individual trade unions decided at a 
special session today to present Schulte at the DGB Congress 
scheduled to take place in Berlin between 13 and 17 June as 
candidate for the chairmanship. DPA learned this from 
participants in the special session. 
  The 54-year-old official is a member of the Executive 
Committee of the Metal Workers Trade Union and responsible for 
the steel industry and for codetermination. 
  The trade union chairmen rejected a crucial vote at the DGB 
congress between Schulte and DGB Deputy Chairwoman Ursula 
Engelen-Kefer. 

</TEXT>

