<F P=103> BR2405123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Rwanda: Italy Wants Clear Signal </F>
From UN"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Brussels, May 24 -- Italy remains ready to 
participate in an eventual international effort in favor of 
Rwanda but first wants to see a clear decision by the United 
Nations, Italian Defense Minister Cesare Previti said here on 
Tuesday [24 May]. 
  Speaking on the sidelines of the ministerial NATO planning 
committee, the defense minister added, "We expect to see some 
clear ideas. Foreign Minister (Antonio) Martino is sounding out 
available energies in the United Nations" for a humanitarian 
effort. 
  Italy, Previti said, stands ready to do its part as it has 
in 
the past. 

</TEXT>

