<H3> <TI>   Sinn Fein Leader Adams Begins Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sinn Fein Leader Adams Begins Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1905093194 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1939 GMT 18 
May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1905093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Ireland/Italy: Sinn Fein Leader </F>
Adams Visits Italy"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) London, May 18 -- The leader of Ireland's 
Sinn Fein party, Gerry Adams, left today for a five-day visit to 
Italy aimed at informing public opinion on the situation in 
Northern Ireland. 
  Sinn Fein is viewed as the political wing of the underground 
Irish Republican Army and Adams has already made similar visits, 
despite protests from London, to the United States and, last 
week, the Basque regions. 
  Adams is slated to meet in Venice with Martino Dorigo, MP 
for 
Communist Refoundation, and in Turin with another Communist MP, 
Marco Rizza, before winding up his visit Monday with a press 
conference. 

</TEXT>

