<F P=106> [Article signed NI: "Arrival of Polish President Lech Walesa </F>
at Zurich-Kloten"] 
  [Text] Zurich, 25 May (ATS) -- The Polish President Lech 
Walesa and his wife Danuta arrived at Zurich-Kloten airport at 
1040 on Wednesday [25 May] on board a special flight from 
Warsaw. The presidential couple is on a three-day state visit 
to Switzerland. Mr. and Mrs. Walesa were welcomed at the plane 
by Confederation President Otto Stich, Federal Council Member 
Flavio Cotti, and Francois Couchepin, chancellor of the 
confederation, who were accompanied by their wives. 
  The Polish and Swiss delegations, each consisting of about 
20 
people, took limousines to the special train for Bern. The 
Polish president will be received there by the Federal Council, 
after military honors have been observed at the Federal Palace. 
The Polish and Swiss delegations will hold official talks this 
afternoon, after which the Federal Council will host dinner in 
honor of its guests. 

