<H3> <TI>   Results of Poll on `Berlusconi as King' Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Results of Poll on `Berlusconi as King' Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2005104594 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1559 GMT 19 
May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2005104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "14.7 Percent Polled in Favor of </F>
Berlusconi as King"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Milan, May 19 -- Asked if they would like to 
see Premier and Forza Italia leader Silvio Berlusconi as king of 
Italy, 14.7 percent of the 1,016 Italians questioned by Directa 
pollsters via telephone over a three-day period (May 16, 17 and 
18) said "yes." The pollsters, who questioned a sample of adult 
men and women from 95 cities and towns throughout the country, 
made the results known today. 
  Among those most in favor of Berlusconi as king were those 
living on the islands (27.8 percent) and in the south (19.2), 
persons over the age of 54 (20.1), those having little formal 
education (23.1), practicing Catholics (20.7), and housewives 
(more than one in four, while a little over half were against). 
  Among those opposed to "King Silvio" were those living in 
the 
northeast (89.7 percent), students (92.8), industrialists, 
business executives and professionals (89.3), diplomats and 
college graduates (85.2) and males, in general (79.5). 
  Out of the total polled, 74.1 percent responded, while 11.2 
percent said they had no opinion on the matter of Berlusconi as 
king. 

</TEXT>

