<H3> <TI>   Hungary's Jeszenszky: Paris Talks Must Involve Minority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hungary's Jeszenszky: Paris Talks Must Involve Minority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605180894 Budapest MTV Television Network in Hungarian 
1700 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Jeszenszky stated that 
representatives of the Hungarians of Slovakia and Romania must 
also be involved in the preparatory discussions of the Paris 
conference on stability in Europe. His comments came at his 
address to the conference. 
  Jeszenszky said: the Hungarian delegation will be 
formulating 
a separate opinion in the form of an explanatory declaration, 
which will call attention to the fact that the three million 
Hungarians living outside Hungary are not represented by anyone 
at the Paris talks. 

